cafes.name: Gibson's Cat Caf√©
cafes.address: 3820 Dave Ward Dr Suite 1700, Conway, AR 72034, USA

text.text: We got our cat from Gibson‚Äôs 2 years ago and he has been such a blessing. He‚Äôs a great cat and so sweet! I love the concept of getting to hangout with all the cats to see which one is the right fit for you. They‚Äôre all have such different personalities and are fun to play with. These folks are doing such a great job helping cats find their furever homes‚ù§Ô∏ègood job guys!

I have been to the Cat Caf√© at both locations, downtown and its current space, and it has ALWAYS been my no. 1 recommendation for people new to Conway or stopping in for a visit. So reasonably priced and the money spent goes to a good cause! My best friend and I often meet here and hang out and as a native Conwegian attending college in Conway, I tell all of my classmates about this place! Super awesome and friendly people and cats!

I WAS THE FIRST ADOPTER! I love gibsons cat cafe! Every time I have gone it makes me sad to leave. Anyone who loves cats needs to visit! You will want to go back! Anyone who loves coffee should visit! It‚Äôs separate from the cats and you can still peak through the window and see the kitties! This is a SMALL BUSINESS that continues to run and save cats life‚Äôs! My baby was found by the lake, and now she will never know anything but love! GO VISIT GIBSONS CAT CAFE!

cafes.name: The Smitten Kitten NWA
cafes.address: 524 W Sycamore St Suite D, Fayetteville, AR 72703, USA

text.text:
This place is so perfect. You only pay the entry fee then it‚Äôs unlimited time, coffee, tea, and cider. There are lots of kitties & they are very friendly. We had many come sit in our lap and play with the toys.

The worker was very kind and introduced us to all of the cats. We even had a cat greet us at the door. Lovely experience!
Lovely place, all kittens are very cute and have unique personalities. Will definitely come back soon!
All of the cats are well taken care of and absolute sweethearts! They're the cutest things ever, with lots of toys to play withü•∞

cafes.name: Alley Cats Coffee Bar
cafes.address: 305 E Front St, Texarkana, AR 71854, USA

text.text: Outstanding! This is what comes to mind when I think of Alley Cats. The folks there today were awesome, very kind hearted and friendly. The owner talked with us for a while and got one of their alley cats to come out to us. You could see his heart in all he said. Truly one of the best places. The coffees are unique and their savory breakfast waffles with hot honey, just wonderful! Thank you guys for sharing you little bit of paradise with our family! We enjoyed every second.

This place is simply awesome! The staff are super friendly and the coffee is great‚Ä¶ Oh and don‚Äôt forget about the avocado (or banana) toast. If you‚Äôre passing by this place is worth the stop. The decor and coffee shop alone are worth a pit stop and the coffee doesn‚Äôt disappoint. If you want to get experimental, try the spicy Myan mocha (with chocolate or cinnamon). Enjoy!

This place is so fun! One of the most unique coffee shops I've ever been to. Also woman-owned and a big supporter of local artists! The barista was super friendly. The tea and coffee are so good! I'm from Houston but I really hope I can come back! (Also yes it's an actual retired train car but it does have AC and working bathrooms!)

Wow this place is so cute it almost brings a tear to my eye! It‚Äôs not just a coffee shop but also a no kill animal shelter! The volunteers and staff here are not only super informative but extremely friendly. When I walked in with my sister today we immediately noticed the cute senior pups in little pens right next to the front door! The older beagle clearly just had some face growths removed (I mention this because it‚Äôs nice to know that they take good care of all the pets even the seniors). When we got to the counter I noticed tons of cute merch they had cool hats and cute tees. The menu is huge and everything is vegan, they really are putting in the effort to be great to animals and I love that! Grace took our order, she may be one of the nicest people I‚Äôve ever met! She said her sister works down stairs and told her about it and when she came in she decided she wanted to be there EVERY DAY! There are tons of parking spaces outside! The coffee is delicious! I got a peach matcha that tasted just like peaches and cream, and had a cute little peach ring on the straw! I cannot wait to come back here. This is my new favorite place in Arkansas.

Very impressive space! Great lattes, coffee, and smoothies! I am very happy to support this business. Kitty and puppy pets with my morning brew? Yes, please! There is a slide going to the lower level of the building, for those that don't wish to take the stairs! Sculptures, art, and merchandise are throughout the facility, which is also very clean. I am telling all of my friends!

I'm so glad I found this cute, very friendly coffee shop! The caramel vanilla latte made my whole day! Bonus was getting to see the fur babies because it's located in Best Friends Pet Resource Center in NW Arkansas. Highly recommend.

cafes.name: Something Pawsitive
cafes.address: 223 S Pruett St, Paragould, AR 72450, USA

text.text: Super aesthetic and clean establishment with some of the sweetest kitties i‚Äôve ever met. ‚ù§Ô∏è
This is a great place to find a new fur friend or just hang out with some cool cats!

What a magnificent organization! What they do for cats and kittens in their community is amazing! We adopted from them and had nothing but a wonderful experience. Love their hearts for the Lord, and their love and commitment to the cats and kittens in need. If you can, please donate to them, and if you can‚Äôt please share their information to your friends and family!

Branson.name: Mochas and Meows
Branson.address: 3265 Falls Pkwy V, Branson, MO 65616, USA

text.text:
We've only lived here a year and this has become a birthday tradition already. All three of my girls have requested a stop here on their birthday (and each recieved a free cat ears headband for it!). The food is even great! They really are passionate about what they do, and they only receive kitties from the Humane Society.
This place makes you want to bring all the kitties home with you!

So first of all, their smoothies are amazing. Had a Russian blue and it's probably going to be something I crave till I'm back in branson! Second, the cat room prices are so affordable as well. We met little Susan, Gravy, Frankfurt and so many other cats deserving of a family.
They had posters showing the amount of litter and pet food they used. And they had a WHOLE BOARD dedicated to showing what cats could tolerate what kind of person/home life. This place obviously cares for it's cats AND it's employees. Give it a try! You can't get an animal experience, food, and a beverage for anywhere else in branson under 40 bucks!

This place is awesome! So many kitties and great drinks too! The staff is so friendly and if you purchase a drink they had deliver it right to you so you can keep playing with the cats! Very happy this place exists. If you need a pick me up, definitely visit here

cafes.name: Black Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 117 E Main St, El Dorado, AR 71730, USA

text.text: We enjoyed sitting by the picture window with all the natural light coming into the space where we ate our delicious meal.  It was very relaxing. We enjoyed ourselves and the food was excellent.
The food was wonderful & our waitress was the best

Today was my 1st time eating at this restaurant. My friend recommended it. He said he always goes there so I took his recommendation. We were seated at 12:15pm and didn‚Äôt receive our food until 1:45pm. That was quite ridiculous to me. I don‚Äôt blame the waitress, because she‚Äôs not the cook. I might give it a second try the next time I‚Äôm in El Dorado. But in the mean time, Black Cat, improvements need to be made in your service. Your customers are very important.

Compared to the rest of the zoo, the cafeteria has a little that could be improved on. Mainly, ok solely, the food.

It‚Äôs quick to order because there are several kiosks to order from. Food is expensive as it usually is at a zoo. Burger was bleh. I didn‚Äôt eat it all. It was gross actually lol! I enjoyed the free refill zoo cup though!
Food was cold. Cheese on hamburger didn't even melt. Fries would have been good if not cold.

The line went fairly quick and the food was actually pretty good! We got burgers and fries. You can sit and watch the monkeys while you eat altho not sure that's a good idea ü§£. Overall a pretty reasonable priced good place to grab a bite to eat while visiting the zoo.

My friend and I made an appointment to visit on a Saturday afternoon. When we arrived, we were greeted immediately. As this was our first visit, we were given a brief orientation. After ordering our drinks, we went in to meet the kitties. It was a fun hour of petting cats and swapping stories about our own pets with others. When we left, my friend and I agreed that we both felt less stressed and more relaxed than we had been. We'll definitely visit again.

Visited from Chicago and decided to stop by because who doesn't love cats and the coffee is a bonus! No, but seriously the staff was super friendly and I love that they take care of the cats. The cookie I got was really good and so was my iced chai. Pretty affordable too! The cats were all super cute and overall it was a fun experience.

A really lovely place to visit if you‚Äôre a cat person! The staff here are very friendly and attentive, both to you and the cats. It‚Äôs clear that they genuinely care about the happiness of every cat living here.

The cats are adorable, each with their own unique personality. Some are especially affectionate and will completely melt your heart!

The price is affordable‚Äî$12 includes admission and a selection of drinks, such as iced tea or coffee, at no extra cost. However, some specialty drinks require an additional fee. It would be even better if visitors could stay longer than an hour!

This makes the pricing explanation clearer and aligns with what you want to convey.

cafes.name: Bow Wow & Meow Bakery & Boutique
cafes.address: 11607 Maumelle Blvd, North Little Rock, AR 72113, USA

text.text: Bow Wow & Meow did it for us again! This is the 5th consecutive year we have used them for our pup‚Äôs birthday cake. They always come out PAWfect! This year, a winter storm was going to effect our pick up date so the kind people at Bow Wow & Meow made a rush (and I mean RUSH) order on it so our Jax wouldn‚Äôt go without in his actual birthday. Excellent customer service!!

Beautiful birthday cake for our fur baby! We wanted a patriotic theme since he was born on July 5th. We love this shop and the staff was friendly and helpful. They have everything a dog parent could need. Highly recommend and we will be repeat customers!

Thank you for the peanut butter ball. They loved it. It is full of yogurt drops and carob imitation chocolate for dogs. They devoured it in seconds! The small dog party hat fits perfect. They have everything here you could want for animals. Not to mention customer service is the best. I will tell everyone to stop here for all dog or cat needs!!
